<div id="review_2976687186" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2976687186" />
    <a title="Donna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16855648-donna"><img alt="Donna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1602978915p2/16855648.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2976687186?book_show_action=true">Sep 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Donna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Donna" href="/user/show/16855648-donna">Donna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16855648-donna?shelf=550-to-599-pages">550-to-599-pages</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2976687186" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17783767960092519895">The first part of this book is engaging and interesting. The characters are overly colorful, and the story - though not necessarily believable - moves along at a great pace. Once they leave Twisted River, however, the story seems to blow up in size, and in all different directions. Some parts are in the present time, some are in the past, and others are in the future, making it difficult to follow. I also felt he unnecessarily detoured into politics. All in all, the novel became tedious after aw</span>
  <span id="freeText17783767960092519895" style="display:none">The first part of this book is engaging and interesting. The characters are overly colorful, and the story - though not necessarily believable - moves along at a great pace. Once they leave Twisted River, however, the story seems to blow up in size, and in all different directions. Some parts are in the present time, some are in the past, and others are in the future, making it difficult to follow. I also felt he unnecessarily detoured into politics. All in all, the novel became tedious after awhile.<br /><br />I’d recommend the book to die-hard John Irving fans or those who are stuck somewhere alone, with no internet, no phone, and with only this book for company.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17783767960092519895" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


